  "prompt": "Which San Francisco restaurant has the best okonomiyaki?",
  "response": "Determining the \"best\" okonomiyaki in San Francisco can be a matter of personal taste, but a few popular spots are known for serving delicious versions of this Japanese savory pancake. \n\nOne notable place is Namu Stonepot. While Namu is more broadly recognized for Korean cuisine, they incorporate Japanese flavors and often feature okonomiyaki on their menu. Another popular spot is Toyose, a cozy restaurant located in a converted garage that's famed for its Korean fried chicken but also serves tasty okonomiyaki.\n\nOther places worth trying include Izakaya Kumade and Okoze Sushi, which offer great Japanese dishes including okonomiyaki.\n\nIt's always a good idea to check recent reviews and visit these places to determine which okonomiyaki best suits your tastes.",
